<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: A little help with Final Fantasy II]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12227&amp;p=138985#p138985"><![CDATA[
Open the <a href="http://www.fceux.com/web/help/fceux.html?Debugger.html" class="postlink">debugger</a>, put a breakpoint on PPU writes to the nametable region. You can add a conditional breakpoint like A == #C7 to find where H is being written, etc. (usually writes to $2007 are done with STA, so a condition using A will probably find what you want).<br /><br />Probably you will want to start a trace just before the letter is going to be written to the screen. Enable the breakpoint. Run until the breakpoint is hit and save the trace. At the bottom of the trace log, the value is being written to the PPU, follow it backwards until you find its source.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5165">rainwarrior</a> — Sat Jan 10, 2015 12:23 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
